# Nginx vhost placeholder for TOR .onion access — tenant {{ item.id }}
# Managed by Ansible — NOT currently deployed (TOR routes directly to containers).
#
# This file is a placeholder for future enhancements that require Nginx to sit
# between TOR and the containers. Use cases:
#
#   1. Serving Element Web with a .onion-specific config.json so the client
#      connects to the .onion homeserver instead of the clearnet domain.
#      (Requires a dedicated local port and a separate element_config.json
#      rendered with the .onion homeserver URL)
#
#   2. Adding TOR-specific response headers or stripping headers that leak
#      the clearnet hostname.
#
#   3. Implementing per-tenant access logging separate from clearnet traffic.
#
# To activate: remove the comment block, assign a dedicated local port
# (e.g., element_onion_port), update the torrc to point to that port instead
# of item.element_port, and deploy this vhost.
#
# Current state: TOR's torrc maps .onion ports directly to container ports.
# See: roles/SourceFiles/TOR/torrc-hidden-service.conf.j2

# (No active server blocks)
